org.hibernate.metamodel.model.domain.spi

Interface PersistentCollectionDescriptor<O,C,E>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CollectionDomainType<C,E>, DomainType<C>, DomainTypeDescriptor<C>, EmbeddedContainer<C>, ExpressableType<C>, Fetchable<C>, Filterable, Joinable<C>, Navigable<C>, NavigableContainer<C>, PluralValuedNavigable<C>, RootTableGroupProducer, Serializable, TableGroupJoinProducer, TableGroupProducer, TableReferenceContributor, Type<C>, Writeable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractPersistentCollectionDescriptor

    public interface PersistentCollectionDescriptor<O,C,E>
extends CollectionDomainType<C,E>, PluralValuedNavigable<C>, RootTableGroupProducer, TableGroupJoinProducer, TableReferenceContributor, EmbeddedContainer<C>, Filterable, Joinable<C>, Fetchable<C>
    Metadata and operations on a persistent collection (plural attribute). Works hand-in-hand with both PersistentCollection and CollectionSemantics to define complete support for persistent collections. Unless a customer RuntimeModelDescriptorFactory is used, it is expected that implementations of CollectionDefinition define a constructor accepting the following arguments:
    1. Collection - The metadata about the collection to be handled by the persister
    2. ManagedTypeDescriptor - Describes the thing the declares the collection
    3. String - The name of the collection's attribute relative to AttributeContainer
    4. RuntimeModelCreationContext - access to additional information useful while constructing the persister.
    See Also:
    PersistentCollection
